<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>KZN Health MEC Dr Sibongiseni Dhlomo said the nurse resigned yesterday morning.“The department gladly accepted his resignation because we suspect he was involved in something very bad,” said Dhlomo.He said the resignation didn’t mean the nurse was off the hook, as the department intended to take further action. “The department will continue to take internal disciplinary action against him. “I want to put it on record that we will gather the necessary information from the health centre and take the matter to the South African Nursing Council.“We want them to investigate whether there was any misconduct on his part or if he brought the council into disrepute. “His resignation is not the end of the story.” Dhlomo said the nurse was arrested after a security company conducted a surveillance operation.“I would like to commend the company for conducting a good operation and calling the police to arrest the nurse.”The nurse will make his next court appearance on 17 April.